events.name: Baylor Bears at Oklahoma State Cowboys

headlines.description: Joseph Randle set career-highs by running for 152 yards and four touchdowns, Justin Blackmon matched his career best with 13 catches for 172 yards and two scores and No. 3 Oklahoma State beat Baylor 59-24 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle runs for 4 TDs as Okla. St. whips Baylor

events.name: Clemson Tigers at Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets

headlines.description: Tevin Washington rushed for 176 yards and broke the two longest runs of his career, leading Georgia Tech to a 31-17 upset of Clemson (No. 5 BCS/No. 6 AP) and likely snuffing out the Tigers' national title hopes Saturday night.

events.name: Stanford Cardinal at USC Trojans

headlines.description:
Stepfan Taylor ran for the go-ahead score in the 
third overtime, and Stanford's defense preserved its 16-game 
winning streak by forcing Curtis McNeal's end-zone fumble to end 
the No. 4 Cardinal's 56-48 victory over No. 20 Southern California.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 6 Stanford outlasts USC in 3 OTs

events.name: Washington State Cougars at Oregon Ducks

headlines.description: Oregon stars LaMichael James and Darron Thomas returned from injury but true freshman De'Anthony Thomas sparked the No. 7 Ducks with two second-half touchdowns in a 43-28 victory over Washington State on Saturday.

events.name: Oklahoma Sooners at Kansas State Wildcats

headlines.description: Landry Jones and Ryan Broyles helped No. 11 Oklahoma get back on track and spoil 10th-ranked Kansas State's dream season.

events.name: Arkansas Razorbacks at Vanderbilt Commodores

headlines.description: Zach Hocker kicked a 42-yard field goal with 6:53 left, and eighth-ranked Arkansas rallied yet again to beat Vanderbilt 31-28 Saturday for the Razorbacks' fourth straight win.

events.name: Michigan State Spartans at Nebraska Cornhuskers

headlines.description: Rex Burkhead scored three touchdowns and ran for 130 yards on 35 carries, and No. 13 Nebraska defeated ninth-ranked Michigan State 24-3 Saturday to take control of the Big Ten Legends Division.

events.name: Virginia Tech Hokies at Duke Blue Devils

headlines.description: David Wilson rushed for 148 yards and No. 15 Virginia Tech overcame a sloppy performance to beat Duke 14-10 Saturday for its Atlantic Coast Conference-record 11th straight road victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sluggish Va. Tech survives scare from Duke

events.name: South Carolina Gamecocks at Tennessee Volunteers

headlines.description: Connor Shaw threw for one touchdown and ran for another as No. 14 South Carolina survived Tennessee with a 14-3 victory on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Shaw helps South Carolina survive Tennessee

events.name: Wisconsin Badgers at Ohio State Buckeyes

headlines.description: Ohio St. 33, No. 12 Wisconsin 29

events.name: Missouri Tigers at Texas A&M Aggies

headlines.description: James Franklin's 11-yard touchdown pass to Marcus Lucas in overtime lifted the Missouri Tigers to a 38-31 win over No. 16 Texas A&M on Saturday.

events.name: Purdue Boilermakers at Michigan Wolverines

headlines.description: Fitzgerald Toussaint ran for a career-high 170 yards and tied a career high with two touchdowns, leading No. 17 Michigan to a 36-14 win over Purdue on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Toussaint's big day gets Michigan by Purdue

events.name: Illinois Fighting Illini at Penn State Nittany Lions

headlines.description: Joe Paterno broke Eddie Robinson's record for victories by a Division I coach with No. 409 in Penn State's sloppy 10-7 win against Illinois on Saturday.

events.name: Iowa State Cyclones at Texas Tech Red Raiders

headlines.description: Redshirt freshman Jared Barnett threw for a touchdown and ran for another, and Iowa State shocked No. 19 Texas Tech 41-7 on Saturday night, a week after the Red Raiders won at Oklahoma.
headlines.shortLinkText: Iowa State runs over lackadaisical Texas Tech

events.name: Colorado Buffaloes at Arizona State Sun Devils

headlines.description: Brock Osweiler< threw for 307 yards and two touchdowns, Cameron Marshall added three scores on the ground and No. 23 Arizona State avoided a letdown with a 48-14 rout over Colorado on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Osweiler, Arizona State easily handle Colorado

events.name: Georgia Bulldogs at Florida Gators

headlines.description: Aaron Murray threw two touchdown passes on fourth down, and No. 22 Georgia overcame several mistakes to beat Southeastern Conference rival Florida 24-20 Saturday.

events.name: Ole Miss Rebels at Auburn Tigers

headlines.description: Clint Moseley threw his first four career touchdown passes and Mike Dyer rushed for 177 yards to lift Auburn to a 41-23 win over Mississippi on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Moseley throws 4 TDs to lift Auburn by Ole Miss

events.name: Kansas Jayhawks at Texas Longhorns

headlines.description: Freshmen tailbacks Malcolm Brown and Joe Bergeron combined for 255 yards rushing and four touchdowns as Texas ended a five-game home losing streak in the Big 12 with a 43-0 romp over Kansas on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Texas crushes Kansas behind freshman RB duo

events.name: West Virginia Mountaineers at Rutgers Scarlet Knights

headlines.description: Geno Smith threw two second-half touchdowns and scored a go-ahead TD on a fourth-down, 1-yard run with 6:18 to play as No. 25 West Virginia rallied for a 41-31 victory on Saturday in a game played in a wet, snowy pre-Halloween storm.
headlines.shortLinkText: West Virginia rallies for snowy win over Rutgers

events.name: NC State Wolfpack at Florida State Seminoles

headlines.description: EJ Manuel threw for 321 yards and two touchdowns Saturday to lead Florida State to a 34-0 win over North Carolina State.
headlines.shortLinkText: Florida State routs NC State for 3rd straight win

events.name: Northwestern Wildcats at Indiana Hoosiers

headlines.description: Dan Persa and Kain Colter combined to throw five touchdown passes Saturday, and Drake Dunsmore hauled in a school-record four TDs to lead Northwestern past Indiana 59-38.
headlines.shortLinkText: Northwestern tallies 616 yards to wallop Indiana

events.name: Syracuse Orange at Louisville Cardinals

headlines.description: Teddy Bridgewater passed for two touchdowns, Victor Anderson rushed for 93 yards and a score and Louisville's defense stuffed Syracuse in an emotional 27-10 win on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bridgewater's 2 TDs help Louisville top Syracuse

events.name: Boston College Eagles at Maryland Terrapins

headlines.description: Rolandan Finch ran for 243 yards and two touchdowns, and Boston College defeated Maryland 28-17 Saturday for its first Atlantic Coast Conference victory of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Finch runs for 243 yards as BC sinks Maryland

headlines.description: Appalachian St. 24, Georgia Southern 17

events.name: Navy Midshipmen at Notre Dame Fighting Irish

headlines.description: Jonas Gray ran for three of Notre Dame's seven rushing touchdowns, and Michael Floyd ran for a score and caught another as the Fighting Irish rebounded from a rough week with a 56-14 rout of Navy on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Notre Dame rebounds with 7 rushing TDs in rout

events.name: Iowa Hawkeyes at Minnesota Golden Gophers

headlines.description: MarQueis Gray's fourth-down sprint for the pylon from the 2-yard line in the closing minutes lifted Minnesota to a 22-21 victory over Iowa on Saturday, giving the Gophers possession of the Floyd of Rosedale bronze pig trophy for the second straight year.
headlines.shortLinkText: Minnesota rallies to stun Iowa, claim bronze pig

headlines.description: East Carolina 34, Tulane 13

events.name: Wake Forest Demon Deacons at North Carolina Tar Heels

headlines.description: Giovani Bernard scored three touchdowns and had his sixth 100-yard rushing performance to help North Carolina beat Wake Forest 49-24 on Saturday, making the Tar Heels bowl eligible for the fourth straight season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bernard, North Carolina roll past Wake Forest

events.name: Fordham Rams at Army Black Knights

headlines.description: Max Jenkins ran for two touchdowns in his last game at Michie Stadium and Army rushed through an October snowstorm to beat Fordham 55-0 Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Army fights through snow to shut out Fordham

events.name: California Golden Bears at UCLA Bruins

headlines.description: Freshman safety Tevin McDonald made the first three interceptions of his college career, Derrick Coleman scored three touchdowns, and UCLA bounced back from one of its most embarrassing losses in years to beat California 31-14 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: McDonald picks off Cal to help UCLA rebound

events.name: Mississippi State Bulldogs at Kentucky Wildcats

headlines.description: Mississippi State quarterbacks Tyler Russell and Chris Relf combined for 264 yards and each passed for a touchdown, and Relf ran for two touchdowns in the Bulldogs' 28-16 win over Kentucky on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Two-pronged QB system spurs Miss. St. past UK

events.name: Oregon State Beavers at Utah Utes

headlines.description: John White ran for a career-high 205 yards, Jon Hays tossed two touchdown passes and Utah's defense forced four turnovers as the Utes beat Oregon State 27-8 on Saturday night for their first Pac-12 Conference win.
headlines.shortLinkText: White runs for 205 as Utah earns 1st Pac-12 win
